The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Cup in city on Aug. 29

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The city will not be hosting any of the matches, but Calcuttans will get a chance to get up, close and personal with the ICC Champions Trophy when it will be on display at the City Centre on August 29 from 11.30 am. 

They other cities where the trophy will be on display are Mohali (August 17), Delhi (August 19 and 20), Jaipur (August 22), Ahmedabad (August 24), Mumbai (August 26 and 27) and Bangalore (August 31). 

According to a media release, the 18-inch high and eight-kg trophy is crafted of solid silver and is valued at approximately $ 20,000. 




